   "etag": "\"5NTCbsXue5u92XtxuV0QeM_x9B4/EjPow9WVEp5gPKexDCMqkYoGW8s\"",
   "title": "Here is a common scene in technical discussions, or really any kind of decision-making. Alice: We...",
   "published": "2012-08-24T15:50:09.000Z",
   "updated": "2012-08-24T15:50:10.064Z",
   "id": "z132cvxpnse5zbthr04ce545ymaigp1zoec",
   "url": "https://plus.google.com/116810148281701144465/posts/Xk42rngji5y",
   "actor": {
    "id": "116810148281701144465",
    "displayName": "Russ Cox",
    "name": {
     "familyName": "Cox",
     "givenName": "Russ"
    },
    "url": "https://plus.google.com/116810148281701144465",
    "image": {
     "url": "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-pujw2EWQuvw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/_iIJW42AXCA/photo.jpg?sz=50"
    }
   },
   "verb": "post",
   "object": {
    "objectType": "note",
    "content": "Here is a common scene in technical discussions, or really any kind of decision-making.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eAlice: We should do X.\u003cbr /\u003eBob: We considered doing X, but X turns out to be quite difficult, or has difficult implications (gives details).\u003cbr /\u003eAlice: You don&#39;t understand: X is \u003ci\u003eeasy\u003c/i\u003e.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI have played both roles in this scene many times.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eSometimes Bob is right. He understands the problem more deeply than Alice, and although X appears to be simple, it has far-reaching consequences for both implementation and effect on the surrounding system. It can be quite hard to bring Alice&#39;s point of view around to understanding those.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eSometimes, Alice is right. She understands those consequences but also understands a way to think about X that makes the difficulties melt away. It can be quite hard to bring Bob&#39;s point of view around to understand X in that same way.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eWho is right depends on who has the better (more complete, more useful, more accurate, more correct) point of view. To reach an agreement, one of Alice and Bob must both come to understand the other&#39;s point of view and also come to understand why that point of view is better.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThat means that when you&#39;re a player in or even an observer of one of these scenes, it is very difficult to tell who is right. Even once the scene concludes, even if agreement is reached, it can be difficult to be sure that the right point of view was adopted.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eRemember that the next time you find yourself playing Alice or Bob.",
